{"lemma":"مُدَّة","slug":"مُدَّة","root":"م.د.د","root_slug":"م-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/م-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","prep"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38303","n38313","n38314","n38315","n43533"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"period of time, interval"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"duration"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"term (limited period of time)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"maddah (Arabic diacritic placed over alif, indicating a glottal stop followed by a long vowel)"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"during, within, in the course of","examples":[{"text":"فَأَسْرَعَ جُحَا إِلَى حِذَائِهِ... لَبِسَهُ... وَمَشَى مُدَّةَ سَاعَتَيْنِ... ثُمَّ جَلَسَ وَحِيدًا بَعْدَ أَنْ تَعِبَ مِنْ الْمَشْيِ...","english":"So Joha hurried to his shoes... put them on... walked for two hours... then he sat alone after he got tired of walking..."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/mud.da/","/mad.da/","/mud.da.ta/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38303","headword_ar":"مَدَّهُ","root":"md","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a bihi","text_ar":"مَدَّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"md~dhu","text_ar":"مدّدهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [or this has an intensive or a frequentative signification;] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tmd~dhu","text_ar":"تمدّدهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mAd~hu","text_ar":"مادّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mAddhu","text_ar":"ماددهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in different copies of the K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mumaAd~apN","text_ar":"مُمَادَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midaAdN","text_ar":"مِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drew it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely a rope, &c., A);"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pulled it: strained it: extended it by drawing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pulling; stretched it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K, El-Basáïr.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a Alqawosa","text_ar":"مَدَّ القَوْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drew the bow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Msb, K, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nzE","text_ar":"نزع"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a mina Albiy^ori","text_ar":"مَدَّ مِنَ البِيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drew water from the well"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mtH","text_ar":"متح"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [Hence, app.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a biA^arofaAdiY","text_ar":"مَدَّ بِاَرْفَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rifodN","text_ar":"رِفْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAy^ilu","text_ar":"قَايِلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalimapi Alz~uwri waAl~a*iY yamud~u biHabolihaA fiY AlA_ivomi sawaA='N","text_ar":"كَلِمَةِ الزُّورِ وَالَّذِى يَمُدُّ بِحَبْلِهَا فِى الاـِثْمِ سَوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The utterer of falsehood and he who transmits it are in respect of the sin alike"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a trad. of 'Alee; in which the utterer of the falsehood is likened to him who fills the bucket in the lower part of the well, and the relater thereof to him who draws the rope at the top. (L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a","text_ar":"مَدَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He extended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stretched forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"his hand or arm, foot or leg, &c. (The Lexicons passim.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonanaA","text_ar":"بَيْنَنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamad~adonaAhu","text_ar":"تَمَدَّدْنَاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We drew, pulled, strained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stretched, it between us,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) [But in a copy of the M, it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaAdadonaAhu","text_ar":"تَمَادَدْنَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a AlHarofa","text_ar":"مَدَّ الحَرْفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lengthened the letter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a Sawotahu","text_ar":"مَدَّ صَوْتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prolonged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strained, his voice"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as the Arab does in chanting]: (L:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlS~awoti","text_ar":"فِى الصَّوْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamad~ada","text_ar":"تَمَدَّدَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda AlwaEiydi","text_ar":"عِنْدَ الوَعِيدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He strained the voice in threatening"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nmr","text_ar":"نمر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a","text_ar":"مَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(his sight)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, stretched, and raised,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY $aYo'K","text_ar":"اـِلَى شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a baSarahu","text_ar":"مَدَّ بَصَرَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY $aYo'K","text_ar":"اـِلَى شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stretched, and raised, his sight towards a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * L.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madadotu EayoniY A_ilaY ka*aA","text_ar":"مَدَدْتُ عَيْنِى اـِلَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I looked at such a thing desirously."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, El-Basáïr.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~aha","text_ar":"مَدَّهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He expanded it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stretched it out:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he extended it, elongated it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lengthened it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~ A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"مَدّ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God expanded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stretched out, and made plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level, the earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, L.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"مَدَّ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~il~a","text_ar":"الظِّلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God extended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stretched forth, the shade."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) See 8. ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a A@ll~`hu fiY Eumorihi","text_ar":"مَدَّ ا@للّٰهُ فِى عُمْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made his life long;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * L;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amd~a","text_ar":"امدَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IKtt.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a A@ll~`hu fiY Eumorika","text_ar":"مَدَّ ا@للّٰهُ فِى عُمْرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God make thy life long!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b15-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mud~a fiY Eumorihi","text_ar":"مُدَّ فِى عُمْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had his life lengthened."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b16-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ajala","text_ar":"الاَجَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amad~a","text_ar":"اَمَدَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imodaAdN","text_ar":"اـِمْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He deferred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"postponed, the term,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period of duration."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b17-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu fiY AlA^ajali","text_ar":"لَهُ فِى الاَجَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amd~","text_ar":"امدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He deferred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"postponed, to him the term,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his term."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b18-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~ahu","text_ar":"مَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2696},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amd~hu","text_ar":"امدّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imodaAdN","text_ar":"اـِمْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;) but the latter is little used; (L;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to continue; to go on long; left him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"let him alone, long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for a while; granted him a delay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respite."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K. *) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~ahu fiY gay~ihi","text_ar":"مَدَّهُ فِى غَيِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amd~hu","text_ar":"امدّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to continue, &c., in his error."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a A@ll~`hu lahu fiY AlEa*aAbi","text_ar":"مَدَّ ا@للّٰهُ لَهُ فِى العَذَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made him to continue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go on long, in a state of punishment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) See also 3. ―         -b19-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a fiY Als~ayori","text_ar":"مَدَّ فِى السَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made much advance in journeying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b20-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~ahu","text_ar":"مَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madadN","text_ar":"مَدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midaAdN","text_ar":"مِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it much in quantity; increased it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) ―         -b21-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a","text_ar":"مَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", [contr. to analogy,] (L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(water, L, and a river, S, L, and a sea, or great river, L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(water, L, and a sea, or great river, L, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"increased;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amd~","text_ar":"امدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; both of which verbs are also used transitively: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became much in quantity, copious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant, in the days of the torrents;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amtd~","text_ar":"امتدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazara","text_ar":"جَزَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it ebbed]. (Lth, S, M, K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jzr","text_ar":"جزر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b22-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAdiY ka*aA yamud~u fiY nahori ka*aA","text_ar":"وَادِى كَذَا يَمُدُّ فِى نَهْرِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a valley flows into and increases such a river."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L.) ―         -b23-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~ahu","text_ar":"مَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, S, L, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, L, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amd~hu","text_ar":"امدّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entered into it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e., a like thing,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and increased it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it copious"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a river, S, L, or sea, or great river, L, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed into it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e., another river, or sea, or great river,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and increased it, replenished it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it copious"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * L, Msb: *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a well)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fed it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., another well: (L:) [see an ex. in a verse cited in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"grw","text_ar":"غرو"},{"kind":"text","text":", conj. 3]: both these verbs are also used intransitively. (Msb.) ―         -b24-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~~ti Als~uwqu","text_ar":"مَدّّتِ السُّوقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The market was full of people and of goods for sale."},{"kind":"text","text":"See the part. n.] ―         -b25-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a Alqawoma","text_ar":"مَدَّ القَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became an auxiliary to the people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madadonaAhumo","text_ar":"مَدَدْنَاهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We became auxiliaries to them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"somewhat differing from ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amadonaAhumo","text_ar":"اَمَدْنَاهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We aided them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"succoured them, by others than ourselves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, L, K:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimadadK","text_ar":"بِمَدَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amodadotuhu","text_ar":"اَمْدَدْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I aided him, and strengthened him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"increased his numbers and strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with an army:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amiyru junodahu biAlxayoli waAlr~ijaAli","text_ar":"الاَمِيرُ جُنْدَهُ بِالخَيْلِ وَالرِّجَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amad~a","text_ar":"اَمَدَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The commander aided,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"succoured, his army with cavalry and infantry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with horses and men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimaAlK kaviyrK","text_ar":"بِمَالٍ كَثِيرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amd~humo","text_ar":"امدّهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He aided them with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave them, much wealth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and [it is said in the Kur, lii. 22,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^amodadonaAhumo bifaAkihapK","text_ar":"وَاَمْدَدْنَاهُمْ بِفَاكِهَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And We will increase their provision time after time with fruit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Beyd, Jel:) or with relation to evil, you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madadotuhu","text_ar":"مَدَدْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and with relation to good, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amodadotuhu","text_ar":"اَمْدَدْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) so says Yoo: (L:) this is generally the case; and the following are examples:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amodadonaAhumo bifaAkihapK","text_ar":"اَمْدَدْنَاهُمْ بِفَاكِهَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[explained above]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"namud~uhumo mina AlEa*aAbi","text_ar":"نَمُدُّهُمْ مِنَ العَذَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ElBasáïr) [Kur, xix. 82,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We will prolong and increase to them punishment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Beyd;:) but Z relates, that Akh said the reverse, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEada","text_ar":"وَعَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoEada","text_ar":"اَوْعَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the usage of the Arabs, however, does not accord with either of these assertions. (MF.) ―         -b26-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a","text_ar":"مَدَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(anything)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became full, and rose."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, L.) ―         -b27-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a Als~iraAja","text_ar":"مَدَّ السِّرَاجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", A, [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put oil"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into the lamp."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, K.) ―         -b28-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a Ald~awaApa","text_ar":"مَدَّ الدَّوَاةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amd~haA","text_ar":"امدّهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put ink into the receptacle thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he increased its water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its ink."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b29-  In like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a Alqalama","text_ar":"مَدَّ القَلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amd~hu","text_ar":"امدّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He supplied the reed-pen with ink."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b30-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~ahu mud~apF mina Ald~awaApi","text_ar":"مَدَّهُ مُدَّةً مِنَ الدَّوَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mud~apF","text_ar":"مُدَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amad~ahu","text_ar":"اَمَدَّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also allowable; (L;) or simply"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~ahu","text_ar":"مَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amad~ahu","text_ar":"اَمَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave him a dip of ink from the receptacle thereof with a reed-pen."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b31-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a","text_ar":"مَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dipped"},{"kind":"text","text":"the reedpen"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the receptacle of ink a single time for writing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) See also 10. ―         -b32-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"مَدَّ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", A, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He manured the land with dung:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he added to the land manure composed of dung and ashes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust and dung,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of strong earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sand; to render it more productive."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b34-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a AlA_ibila","text_ar":"مَدَّ الاـِبِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, S, A, L, K.) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AZ, L;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amd~hA","text_ar":"امدّها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madiyd","text_ar":"مَدِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water upon which had been sprinkled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which had been mixed, some flour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the camels to drink:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, A, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he put some barley coarsely ground, and then moistened, into the camel's mouths:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, L:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~ahu bimadiydK","text_ar":"مَدَّهُ بِمَدِيدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~N","text_ar":"مَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he fed him with fodder."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","Lh","Msb","AZ","Beyd","Jel","A"]},{"entry_id":"n38313","headword_ar":"مَدَّةٌ","root":"md","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single act of drawing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pulling; of straining; of stretching; &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) ―         -b2-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mud~apu","text_ar":"مُدَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n38314","headword_ar":"مُدَّةٌ","root":"md","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utmost,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extreme, extent, term, limit, reach,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point, of time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lih`*ihi AlA^um~api mud~apN","text_ar":"لِهٰذِهِ الاُمَّةِ مُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To this nation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people, is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an extreme term of endurance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mud~apN","text_ar":"مُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long space of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any space of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burohapN","text_ar":"بُرْهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion of time, whether little"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midaAdN","text_ar":"مِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mud~apN","text_ar":"مُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dip of ink;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity of ink that is taken upon the reed-pen."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * K.) The vulgar say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~apN","text_ar":"مَدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mid~apN","text_ar":"مِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","IAth","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n38315","headword_ar":"مِدَّةٌ","root":"md","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thick purulent matter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayoHN","text_ar":"قَيْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that collects in a wound:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L:) the thin is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadiydN","text_ar":"صَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, Msb.) ―         -b2-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mud~apN","text_ar":"مُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["A","Msb","S","L","K"]},{"entry_id":"n43533","headword_ar":"مَدَهَ","root":"mdh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madaHa","text_ar":"مَدَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}